Author-Name:    Osband, Kent
Title:   Economic Crisis in a Shortage Economy. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 673-90
Issue: 4
Volume: 100
Year: 1992
Month:  August 
Abstract:
  It is not unusual for reforming socialist economies to relax wage
 controls without hardening budget constraints on enterprises or freeing
 consumer goods prices. This policy can be dangerously destabilizing. While
 higher wages permit workers to purchase more of some goods, they also tend
 to exacerbate shortages and to breed waste and corruption. Beyond a
 certain level, economywide wage hikes will worsen worker welfare,
 regardless of whether deficit goods are strictly rationed, sold randomly
 at official prices to queuing workers, or offered to workers by "insiders"
 only at black-market prices. However, the form of allocation does
 influence the levels of output and welfare.  Copyright 1992 by University of Chicago Press.
