Author-Name:  Kehoe, Patrick J
Author-Name:  Kydland, Finn E
Title:   International Real Business Cycles. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 745-75
Issue: 4
Volume: 100
Year: 1992
Month:  August 
Abstract:
  The authors ask whether a two-country business cycle model can account
 simultaneously for domestic and international aspects of business cycles.
 With this question in mind, the authors document a number of discrepancies
 between theory and data. The most striking discrepancy concerns the
 correlations of consumption and output across countries. In this data,
 outputs are generally more highly correlated across countries than
 consumptions. In the model they see the opposite.  Copyright 1992 by University of Chicago Press.
